records.addlTxt:
Defendant Shauniqua C Johnson in court with attorney Stephen A Sargent.  Deann L Heard appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

The Court imposed but stayed 4 months at the House of Correction, with Huber for work, school and child care; good time allowed; credit for 4 days time served.  The Court placed defendant on probation for one (1) year.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment if needed;
 - Urine screens;
 - Obtain high school diploma, HSED or GED;
 - No driving without a valid driver's license or without insurance;
 - Parenting counseling;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Perform 20 hours community service;
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements; pay supervision fees.  Failure to pay would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant which is non-dishchargable in bankruptcy.

Filed,
Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
